comment: In the UK, The Sun is well known for printing utter bollocks at times. Their journalists, not all, but a lot of them, are like bushwackers, and the editor is no better. I was called by the editor of The Sun once regarding an 'alleged' sighing of a Great White Shark off the coast of Cornwall going on a photo taken by a fisherman. Now, being Cornishman and hailing from an historical fishing town on the S. Coast, I know my sharks, in fact, I am a marine biologist and coastal ecologist (BSc Hons). I advised the editor that what they had said was wrong, they misquoted the marine biologist regarding the ID of the shark (I later spoke to this marine biologist who is respected within the industry who was rather upset), and went on to say,  her very words "We just wanted to 'sell' a good story". This angered me as the 'story' is utter nonsense - the photo taken was of a 12-14 ft juvenile Basking Shark, I've seen them up close enough times in my life, as well as Blues, Mako and Thresher. As my town used to have a Sharking Club (I know, it's bad, but this was only so from 1930s - 1990 I believe, where now it's just an Angling Club). As stated I was agitated and replied to the Editor "Listen, to be perfectly honest with you, people don't want a 'good story', they want the 'truth' when it comes to the news, and this isn't it, it's not a Great White, it's a Basking Shark". I can't recall her words exactly after, but, she did ask if she could contact me in future regarding shark IDs to which I said that is fine, ending with "At least then people will know the truth", which was a low blow, but, journalists are like vultures (the bad ones who write lies). It's a bit long, I do apologise, I just thought I'd give you the scoop on The Sun.
author: PortbyhanMan

comment:
Trust me when I tell you that I think Amber is full of dung and she absolutely looks like the abuser.  My only criticism of this video is that I'm surprised that you didn't point out some of Johnny's weird body language when he was describing what happened at around the 10:45 mark.  He smirks while describing how she smashed/threw a bottle and cut off his finger.  The right side of his mouth definitely wants to pull back into a smile and he's controlling it.  Then immediately following, when he says, "She threw a vodka bottle at me" both sides of his mouth pull into a smile.  That is considered a microexpression bordering on macro.  He wants to smile when he says this but you can tell he is trying to control it.  Now that can mean a lot of things and it doesn't necessarily point to lying but it is very noticeable and an odd quirk for the particular events he is relaying.  As a point of comparison, imagine if Amber did this while she was describing how Johnny beat her up and sexually assaulted her.  It would be a clear conflict between words and expression.
Anyway, I figured maybe you just weren't looking for this sort of thing but then you point it out in Amber's friend's testimony at the end and how when she insisted Amber never told her that she threw anything she looks to be deceitful.  As well as Amber's own testimony where she is stuffing food in her mouth, you point to that as an obvious way of avoiding the questions.  And I agree!  But the fact that you left out his weird delivery made want to write this.  I'm sure some body language experts would not like how Johnny delivered his view of events.

comment:
About the finger incident, there is another clue pointing out to who's telling the truth here. The chopped-off finger tip is the big deal obviously, but what about the cigarette burn ?? Johnny stated that after she had thrown the bottle at his hand Amber had then burnt his face with a lighted cigarette (he actually points at the spot on his face while talking about it during his deposition). The thing is we can clearly see the circular purple mark on this exact same spot on the picture taken at the hospital. So what about it ? It was a real burn, I don't think he took time to put make-up on his face with his non dominant hand (and what purple make-up anyway ?) when he was still bleeding like crazy, in deep pain and afraid to lose his finger... (needless to say the doctor would have noticed if it has been faked, he received professional medical attention, he is famous and he is an actor, his face integrity means a lot, they would have chekced on it too and treated all injuries he could have, even if the finger was the emergency). So Johnny did have a burn on his face on the exact spot he points out when he talks about it and this burn get the shape and size, with a thin darker contour, of the one you'll get from a lighted cigarette applied on your face. Who did this to him ????

Given the situation, it had to be Amber, no question, it can not be a self-inflicted mark given this peticular situation, even if he was crazy like that, in that chaos when things went out of control with the big fight and the chopped-off finger, such a situation would have not let to anyone the opportunity to come to such an extent to schem something like that in the moment to distort the truth to their advantage, it is not possible  when you do have to deal with medical emergency. And what would have been the point in that moment to have that cigarette burn on his face when he already had a serious enough injury and more important when he never said at that time until Amber went to court  that he get it from her, it clearly has never been the plan for him to accuse her, proof is he didn't came out as the victim for years, so why then in that heated moment, in a shock state he would have thought about inflicted to himself a minor injury with no plan ahead about how to use it to his advantage later on ? I'll add, that I actually never heard about a man, specially someone as public and big as Johnny Depp who had thought about claiming he was physically abused by his wife to avoid to pay for a divorce. What would have been the plan ? It is ridiculous, they are absolutly no reason to assert this burn would have been self-inflicted and still it was there.

 Clearly, it would not be anyone from his staff either, then the only other person there was Amber. So if we admit she did it, we therefore agree she was the abuser, not the other way around. Putting a lighted cigarette on your husband's face is a case of domestic violence in which you're the abuser : it is not a "defense gesture". Kicking back, hitting, punching or spitting even throwing object could have been self-defense gesture but burning someone's face with a cigarette is not, it is cruel, it requires to pause, to act with precision and to definately have a certain amount of control upon the situation : it is not something you'll do while fleeing trying to escape someone whose assaulting you. It is a proper physical attack from an abuser (often found in child abuse and domestic violence cases, usually they are located on limbs but, on the face it's alrealy on another level).

 I think this burn itself speaks volume. 

There is also the other vodka bottle, the first one Johnny said she threw right at his head but missed... It is a thing to go for a hand on a counter, but, throwing things at someone else head ? What if she wouldn't have missed and the bottle had hit him right in the face, couldn't have he get a life-threatning injury there instead of the hand injury ?? It is another level of violence to burn someone else face with a cigarette and to thrown a  heavy and dangerous object right to their face. I hope this will be investigated too.

comment:
sounds to me like amber has a cluster b personality disorder probably BPD comorbid with NPD. 
My theory is that most - if not all - domestic abusers are narcissists, specifically Borderline Personalities because of the rage, the desperation, the delusional thinking and the inability to deal with rejection, as well as the fact that it is often only their romantic and personal relationships where they have problems. Borderline's  often feel that without a partner to validate their existence, they don't exist at all. Losing the partner means losing themselves in a very real way. It is a threat to their very existence. Because they fear rejection and abandonment so much, they perceive it in everything, even when it isn't really there. They react to this perceived rejection and abandonment with rage, hysteria and violence in order to punish their partner and force the partner to do what the narcissist wants. This in turn causes the partner to reject the narcissist for real, which leads to more abuse. The domestic abuser narcissist is essentially saying, "What you want doesn't matter. What you need doesn't matter. Nothing about you matters. Only what I want matters, and what I want is for you to stay with me because I cannot face the shame of failure and the rejection of you leaving. You exist only to fulfill that need. If you don't give me what I want - what I need - I will hurt you. If that doesn't work, I will kill you." This is an example of the power and control narcissists believe they have over other people. That belief is absolutely essential to their lives. Everything is constructed around it. When it is threatened - such as by a partner leaving or attempting to end the relationship - this is perceived as life-threatening. This is why they feel murder is a justifiable response. When the loss of a partner equals the loss of the self or the identity, this is then interpreted into a "nothing left to lose" situation. If you add in the revenge and punishment factor that is a core element of all narcissism, you have a situation that has become extremely dangerous. Narcissists who have killed their partners are even known to react with surprise that people don't think it was OK for them to do that. They can't understand why they are in trouble when - in their opinion - they only did what anybody else would do in the same situation.

All the while, we mischaracterise domestic violence and allow the cycle of violence to repeat because we won‚Äôt address root causes.  This means Amber won‚Äôt get the help she desperately needs and her cycle of violence is perpetuated:
I absolutely hold most of our leaders to blame. comment: Thanks for this informative video.  The Sun is a nasty, horrible, right wing rag.  It is owned by Rupert Murdoch, a man of few morals or principles.  For years it lied about the the Hillsborough football disaster, blaming the fans, not the police.  After years of campaigning the truth came out, the police were to blame and the fans exonerated.  The Sun has been doing the same tricks for years.  Since 1970 it published photos of naked young women on page 3 - the notorious Page 3.  Various people tried to stop this, claiming it contributed to rape and sexual assault.  Then in 2011 a No More Page 3 campaign began to get rid of it.  In 2012 Page 3 ended.  The reason they continued with this was because it made money.   I am not sure why they have done this to Johnny - they have always been able to make their readers believe what they tell them.  Perhaps it's a test of their power.  I am sure they will lose - the evidence is not on their side.  Good on Johnny for taking them to court.  Go Johnny go!
